XSS, standing for *Cross Site Scripting*, is one of the simplest forms of attack to a website.

# Browser protections

Chrome implements a *reflective XSS protection*. Read here: <http://lwn.net/Articles/360424/>

It can be deactivated by sending a

~~~
X-XSS-Protection: 0
~~~

[HTTP]() header. Read here: <http://www.vbulletin.org/forum/archive/index.php/t-276212.html>
